<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="133" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,837,1545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1089,1114]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A species of 
<taxonomicName box="[477,634,1089,1113]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Platycephalidae" genus="Thysanophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[477,634,1089,1113]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Thysanophrys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacking papillae on the upper eye, with 
<number box="[1091,1132,1089,1113]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
DSC scales D fin I,VII, A 
<number box="[151,180,1125,1149]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="11.0">11</number>
, a single preocular and preorbital spines and a short snout with SNL going in HL 3.7–4.0 times. C fin with 
<number box="[1422,1436,1125,1149]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="3.0">3</number>
dark bars and a dark saddle crossing back under the entire D 
<number box="[830,840,1161,1185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="1.0">1</number>
fin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="133" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,837,1545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1197,1222]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Description.</emphasis>
D 
<number box="[387,397,1197,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="1.0">1</number>
spines I, VII, D 
<number box="[588,602,1197,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="2.0">2</number>
rays 
<number box="[668,698,1197,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="11.0">11</number>
; A fin rays 
<number box="[839,870,1197,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="12.0">12</number>
; P fin rays 
<number box="[1007,1035,1197,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="19.0">19</number>
(
<number box="[1053,1128,1197,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="19.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="19.0">19–20</number>
); LL pored scales 
<number box="[1344,1372,1197,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="51.0">51</number>
(
<number box="[1390,1422,1197,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="52.0">52</number>
); anterior one bearing a small spine; GR 
<number box="[592,606,1233,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[636,650,1233,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="4.0">4</number>
= 
<number box="[680,694,1233,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="5.0">5</number>
(
<number box="[712,724,1233,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[755,769,1233,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="4.0">4</number>
= 
<number box="[799,837,1233,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="5.1">5, 1</number>
+ 
<number box="[856,871,1233,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="5.0">5</number>
= 
<number box="[901,917,1233,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="6.0">6</number>
); C branched rays 
<number box="[1129,1145,1233,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="9.0">9</number>
; supraorbital ridge with ~ 
<number box="[151,165,1269,1293]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="9.0">9</number>
(
<number box="[180,237,1269,1293]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="11.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="9.0">9–13</number>
) spines; vertebrae 
<number box="[447,478,1269,1293]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="27.0">27</number>
. Villiform teeth in bands on jaws. LL scale pores with 
<number box="[1097,1111,1269,1293]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="2.0">2</number>
openings to exterior (
<figureCitation box="[1354,1421,1269,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1625,1648]" captionTargetBox="[179,1421,708,1589]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,684,1618]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lateral line scale 12, right side holotype of Thysanophrys tricaudata." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/223726/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
Fig 
<number box="[1405,1421,1269,1293]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,837,1545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,398,1305,1330]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Color in alcohol.</emphasis>
A broad dark band over back below entire D 
<number box="[916,926,1305,1329]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="1.0">1</number>
fin; D 
<number box="[1004,1014,1305,1329]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="1.0">1</number>
with a broad marginal dark band; D 
<number box="[1422,1436,1305,1329]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="2.0">2</number>
mostly clear, a few spots on rays; A with spots on rays near margin; P with several vertical dark bars; pelvic fin with a broad dark band near middle; and C with a broad basicaudal dark band, a dark marginal band and a narrower submarginal band.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="133" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,837,1545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1450,1474]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Remarks.</emphasis>
Although 
<taxonomicName box="[443,588,1449,1473]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Platycephalidae" genus="Thysanophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tricaudata">
<emphasis box="[443,588,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">T. tricaudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fowler, 1938" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" box="[643,927,1449,1473]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Platycephalidae" genus="Thysanophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis box="[643,750,1450,1473]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">T. armata</emphasis>
(Fowler, 
<number box="[862,919,1449,1473]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="1938.0">1938</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
have many similarities, they differ in D 
<number box="[1379,1393,1449,1473]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="2.0">2</number>
ray count (
<quantity box="[229,286,1485,1509]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" unit="in" value="11.0">11 in</quantity>
the former, 
<quantity box="[423,480,1485,1509]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.048" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" unit="in" value="12.0">12 in</quantity>
the latter). In comparing color pattern between the two species (
<figureCitation box="[1212,1290,1485,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="7.[151,250,636,659]" captionTargetBox="[167,1416,179,616]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,165,616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lateral view of Thysanophrys tricaudata, sp. nov., holotype, USNM 268919, 86 mm SL, from Sri Lanka." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/223725/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
Figs. 
<number box="[1276,1290,1485,1509]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[1326,1355,1485,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="8.[151,250,872,895]" captionTargetBox="[193,1399,198,834]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,159,883]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 10. Lateral view of Cymbacephalus armatus Fowler 1938, USNM 90064 holotype 111 mm SL, from Sirun I., Philippines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/223727/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
<number box="[1326,1355,1485,1509]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) major differences in C fin pattern and in dark barring crossing the back are evident.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
